headline: Why Digital Realty Trust Stock Got Rocked Today
summary: It was a case of guilt by association with Digital Realty Trust's (NYSE: DLR) shares on Thursday.  This sent Digital Realty's shares down, too, and the stock ended up closing the day 1.5% lower in value.  In that event, Equinix divulged that its adjusted funds from operations (AFFO) -- widely considered the most crucial profitability metric for REITs -- would take a hit in the near future.

headline: Solar stocks climb, Equinix's weak outlook: Trending Tickers
summary: Market Domination host Josh Lipton goes over some of today's trending tickers with Yahoo Finance anchor Julie Hyman and Christine Short, head of corporate event research at Wall Street Horizon. Solar stocks, like Enphase (ENPH), First Solar (FSLR), and SolarEdge (SEDG), surge after there was renewed talk in Congress of restoring clean energy tax credits. Equinix (EQIX) stock slid on the company's weaker-than-expected revenue forecast. The company also announced costly artificial intelligence (AI)–driven expansion plans that analysts say will hurt earnings. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination here.

headline: Why Shares in This Data Center REIT Slumped Today
summary: The company's analyst day presentation failed to impress investors.  Shares in data center company and real estate investment trust (REIT) Equinix (NASDAQ: EQIX) were lower by nearly 10% by noon ET today.  The decline comes after a slew of Wall Street analysts downgraded the stock the day after its analyst day presentation.
